1.title: Enter the Worthy
1.plot: 12 contestants enter Kampung Quest and have to quickly adapt to an unpredictable and thrilling journey ahead.

2.title: Welcome to the Jungle
2.plot: Langit and Marikh have a taste of the outdoors. The Urbanites compete in their first ever quest. Alliances are in question as members of SIC and Squad Goals are split into different camps. The tension between Chris and Zilpha escalates as it spills onto the battlefield.

3.title: Sky High, Battle Cry
3.plot: Marikh begin to feel the effects of living in the harsh jungle. A demoralized Langit prepare for the crucial Elimination Quest. One camp will face the Campfire. Which would it be?

4.title: Never in Kampung Quest History ...
4.plot: A new day for Langit as they lick their wounds and move on. With Ian gone, the SIC alliance between him, Sau Mun and Chris is down to 2 members. However, grumbling in Marikh sees camp members get on each others' nerves.

5.title: The Fall of Marikh
5.plot: Following a dramatic defeat, Marikh implodes from inside as Urbanites start playing the blame game. An emotional Campfire sees the dismantling of the once glorious, Marikh.

6.title: Braving the Storm
6.plot: Reeling from a double elimination, Marikh are determined to fight back. A twist deals a shocking blow to the camps, leaving them in pieces.

7.title: It's Been a Very Tough Day
7.plot: Both camps face off in a crucial Elimination Quest. One camp faces the Campfire, effectively dismantling it, sending emotions sky high.

8.title: An Evening at the Campfire
8.plot: Spirits are lifted for Langit as they enjoy their much deserved reward for winning the last quest. In another shocking twist, both camps enter the campfire.

9.title: The Once Mighty Marikh
9.plot: Azman comes to terms with the current state of the once mighty Marikh. Sau Mun and Oswald ponder their fate as the other Langit members contemplate who to eliminate next, should they face the Campfire.

10.title: The Game Is Evolving
10.plot: With Marikh facing the Campfire, who will be sent home? Meanwhile, a secret deal is offered to members of both camps.

11.title: Integration by Segregation
11.plot: Amelia's deal goes into effect, swapping members from both camps.

12.title: Trials by Tribulation
12.plot: A quest of speed and strategy sees both camps clash at the Elimination Quest. Nik Danial and 2 others take part in a mysterious quest - The Totem Trials.

13.title: Colours
13.plot: With Aqilah in possession of the Exemption Totem, Nik and Jolene get closer. Azman grows weary as he struggles to adapt with the others. Six urbanites remaining, what's the next big twist in Kampung Quest?

14.title: Imbalance
14.plot: Hati faces their first ever Campfire, setting the stage for the 5 remaining urbanites on Kampung Quest.

15.title: The Fire That Won't Burn Out
15.plot: A tense quest causes the urbanites to bicker amongst themselves, leaving them emotional and broken.

16.title: Resurgence
16.plot: It's make it or break it for Sau Mun as her only chance of survival is to win the next Elimination Quest.

17.title: Heroes
17.plot: An unexpected visit leaves our urbanites emotional. Three more episodes as we come to the final 3 in Kampung Quest.

18.title: The Langit Alliance
18.plot: It's down to the last 3. With the Exemption Totem on hand, it's now or never as they vie for their place in the finals.

19.title: The Unrivalled
19.plot: All the urbanites converge at the Final Campfire. It's time to vote. Who will be the Kampung Quest: Unrivalled Winner?

1.title: The Adventure Begins
1.plot: 10 urban Malaysians are introduced and divided into 2 camps; Merapi and Merantau.The camps experience their first Reward Quest and Elimination Quest.

2.title: Soaked
2.plot: Merantau Camp spend their first night outdoors while Merapi enjoys the comfort of the Kampung House. A delicious Reward Quest precedes the toughest endurance Quest yet.

3.title: The Art of Sleeping Outside
3.plot: Tensions rise after the 'twist' at the last campfire. Both camps compete fiercely to remain in the game.

4.title: Sink or Swim
4.plot: The stronger Urbanites are starting to take the lead but physical strength does not necessarily give you an edge.

5.title: Live the Adventure
5.plot: The Urbanites are put to the test on all they have learnt so far. The competition intensifies as they approach the last few days of Kampung Quest.

6.title: The Cultured Three
6.plot: The events play out from the last episode of Kampung Quest; a double elimination is announced - which leaves just 3 remaining urbanites. With just one day left in the kampung, which two Urbanites will make it to The Final Campfire?

7.title: The Final Campfire
7.plot: The epic conclusion to Malaysia's first independent adventure reality TV show. As all the Urbanites gather for one final Campfire, who will be crowned Champion of Kampung Quest?

8.title: Recapitulate
8.plot: In this special, uncut recap episode, we look back at the first 4 days on Kampung Quest. This mini episode features extended, never-before-seen footage, more drama and more excitement on the authentic Malaysian adventure, Kampung Quest.

1.title: The Adventure Begins Again
1.plot: 10 Malaysians will embark on an epic journey set in the great Malaysian outdoors. They will compete against each other in physical, social and mental quests. These urbanites have to adapt to survive and ultimately overcome the challenges before them. Only the worthy will triumph over all and live the adventure that is Kampung Quest. The 10 urbanites enter the world of Kampung Quest. They embrace the new surroundings and forge new ties. The Selection Ring sees them divided into two camps, Obor and Muara. Muara is sent to the jungle, where they have to learn to adapt to...

2.title: Two Sides of the River
2.plot: Muara camp struggle to find their feet in the outdoors. While the Obor camp reap the benefits of the kampung house. In a test of strength, both camps lock horns in an explosive physical quest. The strain of the outdoors see Muara camp members in conflict with Aveena. Obor is determined to redeem the kampung house as Muara is desperate to win it back. Both camps go head-to-head in an intense Elimination Quest that will send Muara to the Campfire.

3.title: One Step Forward, Two Steps Back
3.plot: A despirited Muara soon face the Campfire. Obor fully embrace the kampung life, while Muara spends another rough day in the jungle. A twist of fate sees both camps divided. At the Campfire, Muara sends home Aveena. Camp spirits is high as Obor adapt well to their surroundings. In a shocking twist, Ashley of Muara switches over to Obor with Jason going the opposite way.

4.title: Self Sacrifice
4.plot: Ashley and Jason adapt to their new camps. Obor and Muara face off in the Elimination Quest, ending with a dramatic turn of events. Muara rally together to defeat Obor in the Elimination Quest. At the Campfire, Obor make the tough decision to send Pik Ming home.

5.title: Gettin' Down & Dirty
5.plot: In the dead of night, a surprise announcement is made to Muara. Obor and Muara take each other to the ground in a brutal physical quest. A kampung situation sees Dini and Jason of Muara venture into water pipes and return with an Exemption Totem. In the most physical Quest yet, both camps get down and dirty when Obor sends Muara to the Campfire.

6.title: True Calling
6.plot: Revelations that come to light do not bode well for some. Tensions rise in Muara as they struggle to keep together. The Confession Ring lays bare the truth between urbanites. Muara unanimously vote for Boey to be sent home. Tensions reach boiling points in Muara between Dini and Jason.

7.title: Torn Between Two Brothers
7.plot: Both camps face a crucial Quest that tests their spirit and determination, leaving the losing camp in pieces. Both camps face off in a physical Quest. Cindy of Obor defeats Dini of Muara, to send Muara to the Campfire. Dini mentally breaks down and gives the Exemption Totem to Thivian over Jason.

8.title: Changing Lanes
8.plot: With disharmony growing within Muara's ranks, they face an intense Campfire. The Quest gets tougher as the urbanites are moved to a new location. An attractive deal is offered, but at what price? Muara face the Campfire with both Dini or Jason expecting to be sent home. In a sudden twist, it is revealed it will be not an elimination Campfire. The Quest intensifies as the urbanites are relocated to the new locations. Thivian accepts the deal to intentionally lose the next Quest in exchange for exemption.

9.title: Playing the Game
9.plot: Does Thivian keep to the deal and intentionally lose the next Elimination Quest for Muara? Having accepted the deal, Thivian loses the Elimination Quest for Muara in exchange for exemption at the Campfire. Muara face the Campfire for the fourth time and sends Jason home. Muara is down to two while Obor is still strong with four urbanites.

10.title: Live Together, Outlast Everyone
10.plot: A revelation by Mia sends shockwaves to both camps and blows the Quest wide open. Both camps combine together to form a new camp, Matahari. Nik Danial leads Matahari to victory in a gruelling physical Quest. Due to health and safety reasons, Mia pulls out of Kampung Quest. The former Obor camp members attempt to force Dini to use the Exemption Totem. A thoroughly clever plan by Dini and Thivian sees Nik Danial sent home. In traditional Kampung Quest fashion, a bomb is dropped.

imdb.plot outline: 'Kampung Quest' is an adventure reality show which takes 10 urban Malaysians out of their comfort zones of modern city life and throws them into an idyllic rural setting, complete with an authentic kampung house and a river running by. There they compete daily in culturally-themed quests which they must win in order to stay in the show. The urbanites are split into two camps of five; Merantau Camp and Merapi Camp. Depending on the outcome of the Elimination Quest, both camps will either stay in the kampung house or rough it out in the outdoors. Each day consists of three key events; the Reward Quest, the Elimination Quest and The Campfire. In the Reward Quest, both camps compete to be rewarded with sponsored prizes. In the Elimination Quest, both camps compete for basic necessity items (shampoo, inflatable pillow) and to be exempted from attending The Campfire where the losing camp will have to vote out one member from their camp.
